These road features are found on the USGS 1:24,000 mapping series. In some areas, these roadways are current through the 2000 construction season, elsewhere they depict features as represented on the USGS map.</abstract>       <purpose>Basemap preparation, cartographic products, registration, control</purpose>       <supplinf>Statewide</supplinf>     </descript>      <timeperd>       <timeinfo>         <sngdate>           <caldate>01/01/2001</caldate>         </sngdate>       </timeinfo>       <current>The original digitization was done during the 1990-1995 time period. For any given area, Mn/DOT used the most recent USGS 7.5-minute quadrangle available at that time.         <srcscale>Source layer dotrdln3:  24000 </srcscale>       </srcinfo>       <procstep>         <procdesc>Attribute Lineage for source table ROAD_MISCLN3.DBF:  Attributes were derived from data present on MNDOT's web data distribution site located at http://rocky.dot.state.mn.us/BaseMap/. The files were downloaded by MNDNR on 8/24/2001.  The data as downloaded from MNDOT were found to have inconsistencies in the attributes associated with the road features between tiles. There is a group of attributes that are documented by MNDOT which existed within each tile. However, many tiles included extraneous, undefined fields, or duplicated fields within the same table. Changes made by MNDNR include:  a) Redefined original field CODE from a 2 place character field to ROAD_CLASS as a 2 character integer field. This change was made to maintain consistency with the current road data in the DNR Core Library. b) Dropped COUNTYNAME Field. This information can be derived by joining with base table of names using the COUN field. c) Redefined COUNTY_NUM field to correspond to existing department guidelines as COUN field with a 2 place integer field. d) Redefined MUNI_MCD field from a 4 place character field to a 5 place integer field and renamed to MCD_CODE in anticipation of the new municipal and township coding scheme. e) TIS_CODE - This field was dropped. It was determined to be of low value to DNR Staff and could be regenerated from the CODE,COUN,MCD_CODE, and Road_Num fields. f) GIS_ROUTE - Dropped field. g) RDWY_NAME - Dropped field. </procdesc>
